              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">What's the difference between mini gastric bypass and traditional bypass?</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Mini gastric bypass uses <strong>one surgical connection (anastomosis)</strong> instead of two, making it technically simpler. Surgery time is <strong>2-3 hours vs 3-4 hours</strong> for traditional bypass. Both achieve similar weight loss (70-80%), but mini bypass has <strong>slightly faster recovery</strong> and potentially lower complication rates. The single connection means less surgical complexity but may have <strong>higher bile reflux risk</strong> in some patients (5-10% vs 1-3%).
